<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002463.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Mulberry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I was wondering if any other planes-walking types have had any observations on the dropping frequency of Indicolite as compared to other drops on either plane?<P>Over a 72 hour period in Hate over the weekend, only 3 pieces of Indicolite dropped. The (affectionately known as) "karaokes" seem to appear roughly perhaps 2/3 as many times as Spite golems and Clerics of Innoruuk. However, we obtained lots and lots of Rune Etched and Ethereal Mist armor (over a dozen EM and ten Rune Etched).<P>It seems the class most dependent on good armor is getting shafted on the planes. On our server, there are lots of warriors as well, so competition can be very great up there. I was blessed enough to be able to get one of the pieces, but I really feel this armor should be dropping more.<P>Other classes are also being shafted on their planar gear--enchanters and magicians had it even worse (only 1 each of their gear). <P>On the other hand, a warrior is the whole sum of their armor and this stuff just seems way too rare. <P>Any observations from other servers?<P>------------------<BR>Mulberry McQuaid<BR><I>50th Season Wolf of the North<BR>The Tribunal Server </I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Grimdar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yes Mulberry, I've seen the same thing. Over a period of 5 days 4-6 hours each (roughly 25 hours) we saw ONE Indo drop. See my other post regarding Verant finally realizing something is screwed up.<P>------------------<BR>Grimdar Hillmover of Rodcet Nife<BR>50th Dwarven Warrior<BR>35th Dwarven Paladin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">What really bugs me about Verant, is they have taken the "Assume the player is a liar" stance. No matter what evidence is brought forth, and no matter how many people are bitching about it - they still assume we are full of spore...<P>I fully understand the need to be cautious in a game of this size, however - when you have 3000 people bitching about something, you would think that they'd at least investigate it before they shot us down.<P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Raggrok Skullcrusha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Part of the reason we got screwed is that they turned down the drop rate of wandering mobs and there are all of about 10 static mummies in the whole zone.  Most of the mummies that you will see in Hate are wandering mobs (which drop jack), and even still a majority of wandering mobs are clerics, spites, and scorns.<P>The drop rate on warrior gear is now very pathetic and I can only pray that they delay to the patch is due to a drop rate enhancement to Hate.<P>------------------<BR>-Raggrok Skullcrusha<P>50th Ogre Warrior; RZ</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sansfear</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">As Raggrok said, the main problem is the majority of mummies and revenants that you kill are wanderers.<P>The secondar problem is that the static mummies and revenants are generally located on the far side of the zone from the safe (SW) corner.<P>With 7-hour respawn time there it is difficult to clear the entire zone to the east.  This is especially true when most people just want to clear the path to Maestro and Innoruuk and leave the entire east side of the zone untouched.<P>With all the pathing problems in Hate, Verant did a huge disservice to us when they reduced the drops on the wanderers.  Here's hoping that they adjust it back in the next patch (though I'm not holding my breath).<P>Sansfear<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Mulberry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">What about competition in the planes though for warriors? How many warriors are usually with you on your Plane raids?<P>It's not uncommon for some classes (Bards, Shadow Knights, Shaman) to get multiple pieces on our trips do to their small numbers. <P>However, we usually have around 5-8 warriors up on the planes. It just seems like a total disservice to our class.<P><P>------------------<BR>Mulberry McQuaid<BR><I>50th Season Wolf of the North<BR>The Tribunal Server </I></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
